  "prompt": "Who are some of the best lawyers in India?",
  "response": "India is home to many highly skilled and reputable lawyers who have made significant contributions to the legal field. Here are some of the most prominent and respected lawyers in India:\n\n### 1. **Fali S. Nariman**\n   - **Specialization**: Constitutional Law, Arbitration\n   - Fali S. Nariman is one of the most esteemed senior advocates in India. He has been involved in several landmark cases and is known for his expertise in constitutional law and arbitration. He is also a recipient of the Padma Bhushan and Padma Vibhushan.\n\n### 2. **Ram Jethmalani**\n   - **Specialization**: Criminal Law, Constitutional Law (deceased in 2019)\n   - Ram Jethmalani was a legendary lawyer known for his sharp intellect and fearless advocacy. He had a long and illustrious career, having handled many high-profile cases and serving as the Union Law Minister.\n\n### 3. **Harish Salve**\n   - **Specialization**: Commercial Law, Constitutional Law, Arbitration\n   - Harish Salve is a highly respected senior advocate who has represented clients in several landmark cases, including the Vodafone tax case and the Kulbhushan Jadhav case at the International Court of Justice (ICJ). He is also a former Solicitor General of India.\n\n### 4. **Mukul Rohatgi**\n   - **Specialization**: Constitutional Law, Commercial Law\n   - Mukul Rohatgi is a former Attorney General of India and a leading senior advocate. He has appeared in numerous high-profile cases, including those involving constitutional issues and corporate disputes.\n\n### 5. **Abhishek Manu Singhvi**\n   - **Specialization**: Constitutional Law, Corporate Law, Media Law\n   - Abhishek Manu Singhvi is a senior advocate and politician known for his expertise in constitutional and corporate law. He has represented clients in a wide range of cases, including those related to media and defamation.\n\n### 6. **K.K. Venugopal**\n   - **Specialization**: Constitutional Law, Public Interest Litigation\n   - K.K. Venugopal is a senior advocate and the current Attorney General of India. He has been involved in several landmark constitutional cases and is known for his advocacy in public interest litigation.\n\n### 7. **Indira Jaising**\n   - **Specialization**: Human Rights, Women's Rights, Public Interest Litigation\n   - Indira Jaising is a senior advocate and a prominent human rights lawyer. She has been a strong advocate for women's rights and has been involved in several landmark cases related to gender justice and human rights.\n\n### 8. **Gopal Subramanium**\n   - **Specialization**: Constitutional Law, Arbitration\n   - Gopal Subramanium is a senior advocate and former Solicitor General of India. He is known for his contributions to constitutional law and has been involved in several high-profile cases.\n\n### 9. **P. Chidambaram**\n   - **Specialization**: Corporate Law, Constitutional Law\n   - P. Chidambaram is a senior advocate and a former Finance Minister of India. He is known for his expertise in corporate and constitutional law and has handled several high-profile cases.\n\n### 10. **Aryama Sundaram**\n   - **Specialization**: Arbitration, Commercial Law\n   - Aryama Sundaram is a senior advocate known for his expertise in arbitration and commercial law. He has been involved in several complex commercial disputes and arbitration cases.\n\nThese lawyers have not only excelled in their respective areas of law but have also contributed significantly to the development of the legal system in India. Their expertise and dedication have earned them a place among the best lawyers in the country.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
